rows.label: qst102506_msg0001
rows.name:
I need you to open the path
to the Dragon's Stomach.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0002
rows.name:
I used to be able to pass through without
issue... I wonder if the Invidian Divine
Beast has intentionally closed it...

rows.label: qst102506_msg0101
rows.name:
So the path to the
Dragon's Stomach is open!

rows.label: qst102506_msg0102
rows.name:
...Hmm. So there were Parisax at
the entrance to the stomach...

rows.label: qst102506_msg0103
rows.name:
That must be why the path
to the stomach was sealed.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0104
rows.name:
Invidia must have sensed
the Parisax's intrusion
and sealed itself off.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0105
rows.name:
Now that you've eliminated the Parisax,
it must have opened up again.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0106
rows.name:
It's a defense mechanism,
much like how a person coughs
when they have a cold.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0107
rows.name:
It's hard to grasp because
of its size, but Invidia is
a living creature too.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0108
rows.name:
Yes, this has been a great
discovery. Thank you.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0109
rows.name:
Well then, I will head to
the stomach and search for
the Dragon Incense.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0110
rows.name:
I've had enough of being attacked
by monsters, so I'll proceed
while staying well hidden.

rows.label: qst102506_msg0111
rows.name:
Ah, that's right! Could you
tell Pilolo to come and help
me collect the Dragon Incense?
